description: Patagonia: In the Footsteps of Charles Darwin Nature, Travel Documentary hosted by Colin Solman, published by KSM in 2013 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/b/b7/Patagonia-In-the-Footsteps-of-Charles-Darwin-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Patagonia: In The Footsteps Of Charles Darwin Patagonia. A country full of endless expanse of untouched nature. A unique wildlife awaits us here at the end of the world, where only a select few get there. Based on original quotations from his travelogue, the film follows the historic route of one of the most important nature observers and evolutionary scientists of history - Charles Darwin. 1) Buenos Aires to Cabo Bahias The Valdes peninsula on the east coast of Patagonia is a unique natural paradise belonging to the UNESCO world natural heritage. Home to one of the last colonies of elephant seals, this incredible habitat sees these massive and awe-inspiring creatures, weighing as much as five tons, haul themselves to this breathtaking place to live well and rear their young.
